cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a deep learning-based framework for contactless palmprint identification, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design of a soft-shifted triplet loss function, which is a machine learning optimization technique, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning-based palmprint detection, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security aspects of palmprint identification, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the use of publicly available contactless palmprint databases, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
